OL,6,FOn one occasion, she pegged notes to a
OL,7,Fneighbour's fence which were scrawled
OL,8,Fwith insults and obscene language.
OL,10,FThe offending then went online when
OL,11,FRealey published a video of a
OL,12,Fneighbour mowing the lawn to her
OL,13,FFacebook page. The Facebook post and
OL,14,Fthe accompanying video contained a
OL,15,Fbarrage of insults directed at the
OL,16,Fvictim.
